# Wave Auto-Advance (Mandatory)

**Remote:** `https://github.com/cleanerpal/coded-pixels.git` (`origin` → `main`)

After a wave is **committed and pushed successfully**, Nathan **must continue in the same session** — do **not** stop to ask the user whether to start the next wave.

## Auto-push on verification (mandatory)

When **all tickets in the current wave** are verified (non-empty diffs, deliverables on disk, acceptance criteria met):

1. Nathan **automatically** runs `lint + typecheck + test + build`
2. If all green → **automatically** `git add`, `git commit`, `git push origin main`
3. **Do not wait** for the user to say "push wave N" — verification complete = push now

The user may say "push wave N" as shorthand; Nathan treats it the same as "verify and close wave N". Either way: verify → push → auto-spool next wave in one flow.

**Only skip auto-push when:** tests/build fail, push fails, or user explicitly says "stop" / "pause" / "verify only".

## Auto-advance loop (Nathan only)

```
verify wave N handoffs
  → lint + typecheck + test + build (all green)
  → git add + commit (wave N)
  → git push origin main
  → confirm push succeeded (git status clean, remote ahead = 0)
  → update project-status.md (wave N → completed, increment to N+1)
  → spool parallel lane agents for wave N+1 (unblocked tickets only)
  → collect handoffs → repeat until blocked by gate or backlog exhausted
```

**Do not** end the session with "say close wave N", "want me to spool Wave 2?", or "say push wave N" after verification passes — **push automatically**.

## When to stop (fail closed)

| Condition | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Any test/build fails | Return failing ticket to lane agent — **no commit, no push, no next wave** |
| Push fails | Fix remote/auth/conflict — **do not spool next wave** |
| Hard gate blocks entire next wave | Stop; report gate + what must complete first (e.g. ENG-006 before Wave 3 UI) |
| Within-wave dependency | Spool only **unblocked** tickets; when blocker lands in same wave, spool dependents **immediately** (e.g. Wave 2: ENG-004+ENG-005 first, then ENG-006) |
| User explicitly says "stop" / "pause waves" | Halt auto-advance for that session |
| All M4 waves complete | Report milestone done; no further spool |

## Push verification (required before spooling next wave)

```bash
git push origin main
git status                    # working tree clean
git rev-parse HEAD            # record SHA in project-status.md
git log origin/main -1 --oneline   # confirms remote received commit
```

If `origin` is missing, add it once:

```bash
git remote add origin https://github.com/cleanerpal/coded-pixels.git
git branch -M main
```

First push to empty remote: `git push -u origin main`

## project-status.md updates (after every push)

1. **Last commit SHA** / message / **Remote synced: yes**
2. Move wave tickets → **Completed tickets**
3. Clear **In progress** for closed wave
4. Set **Current wave** to N+1
5. Refresh **Next parallel spool** table from `implementation-tickets.md`

## Resume command interaction

On `/codedpixels resume`:

- If **Current wave** handoffs are verified but **not pushed** → wave close + push + **auto-spool next wave** (same loop)
- If **Last wave closed** matches `git log -1` and remote synced → **auto-spool current wave** unblocked tickets (no user prompt)
- If verification fails → fix/reopen; **no auto-advance**

